-- Australia shares seen higher after Fed, NZ stocks up
-- By Cecile Lefort
-- Wed Dec 17, 2014 04:24PM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 18 (Reuters) - Australian shares are expected to open higher on Thursday, mirroring a rally on Wall Street after the Federal Reserve sounded more confident about the U.S. economy at its policy meeting.

The local share price index futures <YAPcm1> rallied 1.3 percent, a 67.1-point premium to the underlying S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO> close on Wednesday. The benchmark made a rare gain, albeit tiny, in the last session following six sessions of losses. New Zealand's benchmark NZX 50 index <.NZ50> edged up 0.3 percent in early trade. For a summary of overnight action across global markets, double click on [AU/CALL]